## 2. Module Details

### 2.1 ChemRAG (Literature Assistant)

```
Input: PDF file path
  ↓
[PDF Parser] (PyMuPDF)
  → Extract text, figures, tables
  ↓
[ChemFig Extractor]
  → Recognize chemical structures (SMILES, InChI)
  ↓
[Chunker]
  → Split into 512-token chunks (with overlap)
  ↓
[Vector Store] (ChromaDB)
  → Embed chunks (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
  → Store with metadata
  ↓
[Retriever] (Hybrid: Dense + Sparse)
  → Query: user question
  → Top-K chunks (K=5)
  ↓
[LLM Summarizer] (Claude Sonnet)
  → Generate structured summary
  ↓
Output: JSON (summary, reactions, data tables)
```

**Token Flow:**
- Input: 15k-80k tokens (1-10 pages)
- Output: 2k-5k tokens (summary)
- RAG retrieval: 10k tokens (Top-5 chunks × 2k each)

---

### 2.2 SynthFlow (Synthesis Designer)

```
Input: Target molecule (SMILES)
  ↓
[Retrosynthesizer] (RDKit BRICS)
  → Generate 1-step disconnections
  → Recursively apply (max depth=5)
  ↓
[Route Expander]
  → Generate 3-5 candidate routes
  ↓
[Route Ranker]
  → Score routes by:
    • Step count (lower = better)
    • Reagent cost (lower = better)
    • Yield estimate (higher = better)
  ↓
[Condition Recommender] (LLM)
  → For each step, recommend:
    • Solvent
    • Temperature
    • Catalyst
    • Reaction time
  ↓
[Safety Checker]
  → Check for:
    • Toxic reagents
    • Explosive intermediates
    • High-pressure/temperature
  ↓
Output: Ranked routes (JSON)
```

**Token Flow:**
- Input: 12k-18k tokens (molecule + database info)
- Output: 3k-5k tokens (routes + conditions)

---

### 2.3 CompChem (Computational Interpreter)

```
Input: Calculation output file (MS/VASP/Gaussian)
  ↓
[Parser]
  → Extract:
    • Calculation parameters (functional, basis set)
    • Raw data (band energies, DOS values)
  ↓
[Analyzer]
  → Compute:
    • Band gap (direct/indirect, at which k-point)
    • Effective masses (electron/hole)
    • DOS peaks (which orbitals)
  ↓
[LLM Interpreter]
  → Generate natural language report:
    • Is this material suitable for photocatalysis?
    • Why is the band gap overestimated?
    • How to improve the calculation?
  ↓
Output: Markdown report
```

**Token Flow:**
- Input: 22k-28k tokens (MS XML / VASP OUTCAR)
- Output: 6k-9k tokens (report)

---

### 2.4 AutoLab (Report Generator)

```
Input: Experimental data (CSV)
  ↓
[Data Cleaner]
  → Handle missing values
  → Remove outliers (3σ rule)
  ↓
[Statistical Analyzer]
  → Compute: mean, std, p-value (t-test)
  → ANOVA (if multi-group)
  ↓
[Plotter] (Matplotlib)
  → Generate figures:
    • Scatter (yield vs T)
    • Bar (yield by catalyst)
    • Heatmap (param sweep)
  ↓
[Report Assembler]
  → Fill LaTeX/Word template:
    • 1. Introduction (LLM-generated)
    • 2. Methods (template + user input)
    • 3. Results (data + figures)
    • 4. Discussion (LLM-generated)
    • 5. Conclusion (LLM-generated)
  ↓
Output: PDF (via LaTeX) or DOCX (via python-docx)
```

**Token Flow:**
- Input: 5k-8k tokens (data summary + template)
- Output: 1k-2k tokens (introduction/discussion)

