## 3. Data Flow Examples

### 3.1 Full Pipeline: "Analyze papers → Design experiment → Interpret results → Write report"

```
User: "I want to design a photocatalyst for CO2 reduction."

1. ChemRAG: Analyze 5 recent papers (→ 250k tokens)
   → Summary: "Cu-based catalysts with N-doped graphene supports show 
      promising activity (90% selectivity to CH4)."

2. SynthFlow: Design synthesis route for Cu/N-graphene
   → Recommended route: Cu(NO3)2 + graphene oxide → hydrothermal → 
      reduction (→ 50k tokens)

3. CompChem: Interpret DFT results of Cu cluster
   → "The d-band center is -2.1 eV, suitable for CO2 activation." 
      (→ 30k tokens)

4. AutoLab: Generate report (→ 20k tokens)

Total: ~350k tokens (single run)
With MiMo 1M context → can process 20+ papers in one go!
```

